HEADWORD: Implausible
<hw>Im*plau"si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>plausible</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>implausible</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not plausible; not wearing the
appearance of truth or credibility, and not likely to be believed.</def>
